 Network Load Balancing
Configure Network Load Balancing (NLB) on Windows
Script:

# Install NLB feature
Install-WindowsFeature -Name NLB -IncludeManagementTools

# Create new NLB cluster
New-NlbCluster -InterfaceName "Ethernet" -ClusterPrimaryIP 192.168.1.200 -ClusterName "NLBCluster"

# Add hosts to NLB cluster
Add-NlbClusterNode -InterfaceName "Ethernet" -HostName "Server1" -ClusterName "NLBCluster"
Add-NlbClusterNode -InterfaceName "Ethernet" -HostName "Server2" -ClusterName "NLBCluster"
Explanation:
Install NLB feature.

Adds Network Load Balancing feature to Windows.
Create new NLB cluster.

Configures a new NLB cluster with a primary IP and name.
Add hosts to NLB cluster.

Adds specified servers to the NLB cluster.
